# MultiSync V 1.0 by cytec
# Let you connect your iPhone to more than one iTunes ;)
# 
# Switch your iPhone/iPod to "Manual add Music" 
# run "local" at the mac you have your iPhone/iPod synced to, then switch to the other Machine and run "2nd Mac"
# it Patches the iTunes Library Files so you dont get the clear Promt...
# 
# If you Connect your iPhone/iPod now you should be able to Access/add your Music from the 2nd Machine, too
#


ENGLISH:

xxd is needed

Please enter your Path to iTunes Library in data.conf

Go to your Machine where your iDevice is connectet to and run the "local" Script,
then copy the whole Folder to your 2nd Machine and run the "2ndMachine" Script.

It Searches for the Library Persident ID and changes it to the one on your First Machine.

If your iDevice is set to "add music manually" you can now add Music from this Machine, too
if not, you can sync but loose the data that is not on this Machine, so i higly Recommend to use "add music manually" 

if anything goes wrong, just run "fixit"


GERMAN:

xxd wird benötigt

Bitte den Pfad zu iTunes Library in data.conf anpassen.

Auf dem Rechner welcher mit dem iDevice Verknüpft ist "local" ausführen, den Ordner auf die 2te Maschiene kopieren und "2ndMachine ausführen"

Das Script such und ersetzte die Library ID des 2ten Rechners mit der des ersten.

Wenn das iDevie auf "Manuelle Verwaltung von Musik" gestellt ist kannst du nun Musik hinzufügen...

Wenn irgendwas schief geht, einfach "fixit" ausführen

